threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a Mirai-variant botnet, specifically designed for IoT devices (MIPS architecture). Its primary malicious behaviors include credential brute-forcing via a hardcoded dictionary, self-propagation using Busybox utilities, and process termination of competing malware. Key indicators include: 1) A massive hardcoded credential list in sub_410d4c (e.g., 'root/vizxv', 'admin/admin1234', '/*6.=_ja'). 2) Automated propagation commands involving wget, tftp, ftpget, and chmod +x. 3) Anti-competitive behavior in sub_4006c0 and sub_404bb0, which scan /proc to identify and kill rival botnet processes. 4) C2 communication logic using standard socket APIs and HTTP GET requests for secondary payloads (e.g., '/dlr.').
